nfighting%2C%20and%20the%20importance%20of%20party%20discipline%20ahead%20of%20the%20first%20phase%20of%20LS%20polls%20on%20April%2019.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22PARTHA%20MAITRA%20AND%20ABHISHEK%20CHOUDHARI%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fmumbai%2Fneed-alliances-to-take-our-vote-share-in-maharashtra-past-50%2Farticleshow%2F109360754.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Explained%3A%202024%20Paris%20Olympics%20In%20The%20Shadow%20Of%20International%20Conflict%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20the%20United%20Nations%20voted%20last%20year%20to%20observe%20the%20Olympic%20Truce%2C%20the%20Paris%20Games%20will%20still%20be%20held%20under%20the%20shadow%20of%20international%20conflict.%20The%20UN%20resolution%20was%20entitled%20%26quot%3BBuilding%20a%20peaceful%20and%20better%20world%20through%20sport%20and%20the%20Olympic%20ideal%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAFP%20looks%20at%20the%20ways%20the%20fighting%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20Middle%20East%2C%20as%20well%20as%20tensions%20with%20countries%2C%20notably%20Afghanistan%2C%20whose%20policies%20run%20counter%20to%20the%20Olympic%20charter%2C%20may%20cause%20issues%20for%20the%20Games%2C%20which%20run%20from%20July%2026%20to%20August%2011.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Russian%20riddle%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia's%20persistent%20doping%20led%20to%20a%20ban%20on%20their%20Paralympic%20team%20at%20the%20Rio%20Games%20in%202016%20and%20to%20bans%20on%20Russian%20athletes%20competing%20under%20their%20national%20flag%20at%20the%202021%20Tokyo%20Games%2C%20and%20at%20both%20the%202018%20Pyeongchang%20and%202022%20Beijing%20Winter%20Games.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20time%20the%20issue%20is%20war%2C%20not%20drugs.%20On%20February%2024%2C%202022%2C%20four%20days%20after%20the%20Beijing%20Olympics%20ended%2C%20and%20with%20the%20truce%20still%20in%20force%2C%20Russia%20invaded%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20international%20outcry%20led%20to%20an%20immediate%20ban%20from%20most%20international%20sports%20on%20Russia%20and%20its%20Belarusian%20ally.%20The%20International%20Olympic%20Committee%20(IOC)%20suspended%20the%20Russian%20Olympic%20Committee%20last%20October%20for%20annexing%20the%20sports%20organisations%20of%20four%20partly%20occupied%20Ukrainian%20regions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20IOC%20is%20keen%20to%20protect%20individual%20Russian%20competitors%20under%20the%20%26quot%3Bnon-discrimination%26quot%3B%20clause%20in%20the%20Olympic%20Charter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20started%20orchestrating%20their%20return%20to%20competition%20in%20March%202023%2C%20and%20authorised%20their%20presence%20at%20the%20Games%20in%20December%2C%20on%20the%20condition%20they%20compete%20under%20a%20neutral%20flag%2C%20do%20not%20parade%20in%20the%20opening%20ceremony%20and%20prove%20they%20have%20not%20%26quot%3Bactively%20supported%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%26quot%3B%20and%20are%20not%20tied%20to%20the%20army%20or%20security%20agencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUkraine%20is%20still%20urging%20a%20ban%20on%20Russians%2C%20but%20Kyiv%20abandoned%20its%20threat%20to%20boycott%20last%20summer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IOC%20estimated%20in%20March%20that%2036%20Russians%20and%2022%20Belarussians%20should%20be%20able%20to%20qualify%20for%20Paris.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20leaves%20the%20recurring%20issue%20of%20how%20representatives%20of%20warring%20nations%20will%20co-exist%20at%20the%20Games.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EGaza%3A%20remaining%20neutral%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IOC%20is%20striving%20to%20remain%20above%20the%20Gaza%20conflict%2C%20citing%20its%20implementation%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Btwo-state%20solution%26quot%3B%2C%20a%20legacy%20of%20the%201993%20Oslo%20peace%20process.%20The%20Israeli%20and%20Palestinian%20National%20Olympic%20Committees%20(NOCs)%20have%20co-existed%20in%20the%20IOC%20since%201995.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsrael%20has%20not%20violated%20the%20Olympic%20truce%20and%20its%20NOC%20has%20not%20annexed%20any%20Palestinian%20sports%20organisations%2C%20but%20its%20retaliation%20for%20the%20bloody%20attack%20by%20Hamas%20on%20October%207%20has%20destroyed%20the%20headquarters%20of%20the%20main%20Palestinian%20sports%20institutions%20and%20caused%20the%20death%20of%20leading%20sporting%20figures%2C%20including%20the%20coach%20of%20the%20football%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENeither%20the%20Palestinians%20nor%20any%20Arab%20states%20have%20threatened%20to%20boycott%20the%20Games%20if%20the%20Israelis%20take%20part.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20leaves%20the%20IOC%20to%20adopt%20a%20two-pronged%20approach.%20It%20is%20relying%20on%20its%20%26quot%3Buniversality%20places%26quot%3B%20to%20guarantee%20the%20presence%20of%20Palestinians%2C%20who%20might%20struggle%20to%20get%20through%20the%20traditional%20qualifiers.%20It%20is%20also%20focusing%20on%20security%2C%20as%20it%20has%20at%20every%20Games%20since%201972%2C%20when%2011%20Israelis%20were%20murdered%20during%20an%20attack%20on%20their%20Olympic%20delegation%20in%20Munich%20by%20members%20of%20a%20Palestinian%20extremist%20organisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EIran-Israel%3A%20escalating%20uncertainty%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20still%20difficult%20to%20assess%20the%20impact%20of%20this%20escalating%20conflict%20on%20the%20Games.%20Warring%20countries%2C%20such%20as%20Iran%20and%20Iraq%2C%20have%20taken%20part%20in%20the%20same%20Games.%20The%20IOC's%20doctrine%20of%20separating%20sport%20from%20politics%20means%20being%20at%20war%20is%20not%2C%20in%20itself%2C%20grounds%20for%20exclusion.%20Again%2C%20there%20are%20worries%20over%20how%20athletes%20from%20the%20two%20countries%20will%20live%20together%20in%20the%20Olympic%20Village%20and%20about%20their%20behaviour%20in%20competition.%20Iran%20has%20punished%20athletes%20for%20shaking%20hands%20with%20Israelis%2C%20and%20urged%20them%20not%20to%20compete%20against%20Israeli%20opponents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EAfghanistan%3A%20discreet%20pressure%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20return%20of%20the%20Taliban%20to%20power%20in%202021%20presented%20the%20IOC%20with%20a%20dilemma.%20It%20wants%20to%20help%20athletes%20and%20support%20staff%20who%20remain%20in%20Afghanistan%2C%20but%20the%20restrictions%20on%20women%20participating%20in%20sport%20violate%20Olympic%20principles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IOC%20has%20been%20demanding%20that%20Afghan%20authorities%20guarantee%20%26quot%3Bsafe%20access%20to%20sport%20for%20women%20and%20girls%26quot%3B.%20The%20IOC%20has%20also%20provided%20financial%20assistance%20for%20athletes%20and%20left%20itself%20the%20option%20of%20cracking%20down%20on%20the%20country's%20NOC%2C%20for%20example%20by%20refusing%20to%20accredit%20officials%20for%20Paris.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20mid-March%2C%20the%20Olympic%20body%20promised%20to%20%26quot%3Bdo%20everything%20possible%26quot%3B%20to%20ensure%20that%20an%20Afghan%20team%20%26quot%3Brespecting%20gender%20parity%26quot%3B%20would%20attend%20the%20Olympic%20Games%20in%202024.%20The%20IOC%20%26quot%3Bdoes%20not%20believe%20that%20isolating%20the%20Afghan%20sporting%20community%20at%20this%20time%20is%20the%20right%20approach%26quot%3B%2C%20said%20IOC%20Director%20of%20Olympic%20Solidarity%20James%20Macleod.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1713319680000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2Fnnsqcp88_macron-paris-olympics_625x300_04_April_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fexplained-2024-paris-olympics-in-the-shadow-of-international-conflict-5459072%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Even%20though%20the%20United%20Nations