title%22%3A%22America's%20F-35%20stealth%20fighters%20are%20going%20to%20be%20flying%20less%20as%20costs%20soar%2C%20watchdog%20finds%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225469%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20US%20Air%20Force%20fighter%20aircraft%20F-35%20performs%20aerobatic%20maneuvers%20on%20the%20second%20day%20of%20the%20Aero%20India%202023%20at%20Yelahanka%20air%20base%20in%20Bengaluru%2C%20India%2C%20Tuesday%20on%20Feb.%2014%2C%202023.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661eeb3520b15f0ff4289a8d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223646%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20US%20Air%20Force%20fighter%20aircraft%20F-35%20performs%20aerobatic%20maneuvers%20on%20the%20second%20day%20of%20the%20Aero%20India%202023%20at%20Yelahanka%20air%20base%20in%20Bengaluru%2C%20India%2C%20Tuesday%20on%20Feb.%2014%2C%202023.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FAijaz%20Rahi%2C%20File%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20US%20military's%20F-35%20program%20is%20very%20expensive%20%E2%80%94%20and%20beset%20with%20challenges.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20new%20watchdog%20report%20found%20that%20the%20lifetime%20cost%20for%20the%20stealth%20fighter%20has%20topped%20%242%20trillion.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20jet's%20availability%20has%20decreased%2C%20and%20the%20Pentagon%20also%20plans%20to%20use%20it%20less.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20military%20is%20cutting%20future%20flight%20hours%20for%20the%20F-35%20%E2%80%94%20already%20not%20available%20as%20often%20as%20it%20should%20be%20%E2%80%94%20as%20the%20program's%20price%20tag%20grows%2C%20a%20new%20watchdog%20report%20revealed%20this%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Pentagon%20estimates%20that%20the%20full%20life-cycle%20cost%20for%20the%20F-35%2C%20which%20consists%20of%20purchasing%2C%20operating%2C%20and%20sustaining%20the%20aircraft%20over%20the%20next%20several%20decades%2C%20has%20now%20surpassed%20more%20than%20%242%20trillion%2C%20the%20US%20Government%20Accountability%20Office%20noted%20in%20a%20Monday%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gao.gov%2Fassets%2Fd24106703.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20eye-popping%20figure%20from%20the%20GAO%20for%20what%20was%20already%20the%20world's%20costliest%20weapons%20program%20is%20much%20larger%20than%20the%20previous%20estimate%20of%20%241.7%20trillion.%20The%20Department%20of%20Defense%20currently%20fields%20around%20650%20F-35s%20%E2%80%94%20of%20which%20there%20are%20three%20variants%20for%20the%20Navy%2C%20Air%20Force%2C%20and%20Marine%20Corps%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it%20plans%20to%20procure%20around%202%2C500%20in%20total%20by%20the%20mid-2040s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20GAO%20also%20said%20that%20sustainment%20costs%20for%20the%20F-35%20program%20grew%20from%20around%20%241.1%20trillion%20in%202018%20to%20about%20%241.58%20trillion%20in%202023%20%E2%80%94%20a%2044%25%20increase%20that%20comes%2C%20in%20part%2C%20as%20a%20result%20of%20the%20aircraft's%20extended%20service%20life%20from%202077%20to%202088.%20Inflation%20and%20use%20play%20a%20role%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226720%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20F-35%20aircraft%20mechanic%20with%20Marine%20Fighter%20Attack%20Squadron%20(VMFA)%20542%20and%20an%20F-35B%20instructor%20pilot%20with%20Marine%20Fighter%20Attack%20Training%20Squadron%20(VMFAT)%20501%20perform%20preflight%20checks%20on%20an%20F-35B%20Lightning%20II%20jet%20at%20Marine%20Corps%20Air%20Station%20Cherry%20Point%2C%20North%20Carolina%2C%20April%2020%2C%202023.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6508c8e912dc4f001a15fc2e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224480%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20F-35B%20Lightning%20II%20jet%20at%20Marine%20Corps%20Air%20Station%20Cherry%20Point%2C%20North%20Carolina%2C%20April%2020%2C%202023.%3Cp%3EUS%20Marine%20Corps%2FStaff%20Sgt.%20Theodore%20Bergan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Pentagon's%20planned%20future%20use%20of%20the%20F-35%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20stealth%20aircraft's%20overall%20availability%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20have%20both%20decreased.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChanges%20to%20planned%20future%20use%20keep%20the%20costs%20down.%20%26quot%3BThe%20military%20services%20have%20lowered%20the%20number%20of%20hours%20each%20aircraft%20is%20estimated%20to%20fly%2C%20which%20has%20contributed%20to%20reduced%20cost%20estimates%20and%20the%20services'%20ability%20to%20meet%20their%20affordability%20targets%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20GAO%20said%20in%20its%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20F-35%20Joint%20Program%20Office%20reported%20in%20a%202020%20Annual%20Cost%20Estimate%20that%20the%20advanced%20fifth-generation%20aircraft%20would%20fly%20382%2C376%20hours%20each%20year%20at%20%26quot%3Bsteady%20state%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20was%20identified%20by%20the%20GAO%20as%20occurring%20in%20the%20mid-2030s.%20In%20a%202023%20Annual%20Cost%20Estimate%2C%20however%2C%20the%20steady%20state%20flight%20hours%20decreased%20by%20nearly%2082%2C000%20per%20year%20to%20300%2C524%20%E2%80%94%20a%2021%25%20decrease.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20F-35%20Joint%20Program%20Office%20and%20various%20military%20service%20officials%20told%20the%20GAO%20%26quot%3Bthat%20this%20reduction%20in%20planned%20flight%20hours%20reflects%20lower%20than%20anticipated%20use%20up%20to%20this%20point%20and%20evolving%20projections%20about%20future%20use%20of%20the%20aircraft%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Air%20Force%20F-35%20Middle%20East%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64999d70c218ba0019a80eed%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221429%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20Air%20Force%20F-35s%20over%20the%20US%20Central%20Command%20area%20of%20responsibility%20on%20Sept.%2030%2C%202020.%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20Force%2FSenior%20Airman%20Duncan%20Bevan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%