ngs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Being%20able%20to%20adjust%20the%20height%20of%20your%20blades%20will%20allow%20you%20to%20produce%20the%20grass%20height%20you%20prefer%2C%20which%20is%20essential%20for%20certain%20grass%20types.%20The%20more%20height%20options%2C%20the%20more%20precise%20you%20can%20set%20your%20deck.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EDurability%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20We%20based%20our%20evaluations%20on%20the%20mower%20components%20that%20we've%20had%20durability%20issues%20with%20in%20the%20past%20and%20considered%20deck%20thickness%20and%20material%20as%20well%20as%20any%20plastic%20elements%20that%20could%20have%20a%20tendency%20to%20crack%20or%20fail%20over%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHow%20to%20choose%20a%20riding%20lawn%20mower%3Cp%3EHere's%20what%20the%20experts%20we%20interviewed%20had%20to%20say%20about%20selecting%20and%20purchasing%20a%20riding%20lawn%20mower%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EConsider%20a%20zero-turn%20mower%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EBlake%20recommends%20choosing%20a%20zero-turn%20mower%2C%20explaining%20that%20it's%20easy%20to%20make%20turns%20with%20them%2C%20they%20don't%20require%20shifting%2C%20and%20you%20can%20control%20the%20ground%20speed.%20This%20lets%20you%20finish%20quicker.%20Zero-turn%20mowers%20take%20a%20little%20getting%20used%20to%20and%20are%20a%20bit%20pricier%2C%20but%20they're%20primarily%20what%20landscaping%20pros%20use%20for%20cutting%20lawns.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ECheck%20the%20maintenance%20and%20warranty%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EBlake%20said%20the%20most%20important%20thing%20to%20ask%20yourself%20is%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20place%20you%20are%20buying%20your%20lawn%20equipment%2C%20will%20they%20be%20the%20place%20to%20help%20you%20in%20the%20future%20with%20service%20and%20parts%3F%26quot%3B%20This%20is%20especially%20important%20if%20you%20don't%20have%20any%20small%20engine%20or%20machine%20maintenance%20experience%20and%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20a%20professional%20is%20in%20charge%20of%20keeping%20your%20expensive%20machine%20running%20smoothly.%20I've%20personally%20spent%20many%20hours%20handling%20messy%20grease%20guns%20and%20banging%20bent%20mower%20decks%20back%20into%20shape%20and%20would%20much%20rather%20have%20had%20someone%20else%20do%20the%20job%20if%20that%20were%20an%20option.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3ELook%20at%20a%20lot%20of%20options%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ESince%20you%20will%20have%20different%20priorities%20or%20features%20that%20mean%20the%20most%20to%20you%2C%20take%20the%20time%20to%20look%20at%20a%20range%20of%20options.%20%26quot%3BTake%20your%20time%2C%20read%20all%20the%20reviews%20and%20specifications%2C%20and%20your%20investment%20will%20pay%20with%20service%20and%20a%20great-looking%20yard%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Blake.%20We%20also%20recommend%20physically%20climbing%20in%20and%20out%20of%20as%20many%20options%20as%20possible%2C%20so%20you%20can%20get%20an%20even%20better%20idea%20of%20what%20it's%20going%20to%20feel%20like%20to%20ride%20on%20for%20extended%20periods%20of%20time.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERiding%20lawn%20mower%20FAQs%3Ch3%3EWhat%20is%20a%20zero-turn%20mower%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20using%20a%20steering%20wheel%20like%20tractor-style%20mowers%2C%20zero-turn%20mowers%20use%20two%20separate%20steering%20levers.%20These%20levers%20allow%20the%20driver%20to%20control%20either%20side%20of%20the%20mower%20independently%2C%20and%20when%20one%20is%20pushed%20forward%20and%20the%20other%20backward%2C%20you%20can%20execute%20an%20almost%20zero-radius%20turn.%20These%20tight%20turns%20are%20a%20real%20time-saver%20and%20reduce%20the%20chances%20of%20ending%20up%20with%20small%20patches%20of%20grass%20left%20over.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat%20size%20mower%20should%20I%20get%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20up%20to%20you%20how%20big%20of%20a%20mower%20you're%20comfortable%20handling%20or%20paying%20for%2C%20but%20the%20general%20rule%20of%20thumb%20is%2C%20the%20larger%20your%20lawn%2C%20the%20wider%20you%20probably%20want%20your%20mower%20deck%20to%20be.%20This%20is%20because%20the%20wider%20your%20deck%2C%20the%20more%20grass%20you'll%20be%20cutting%20with%20each%20pass%2C%20and%20the%20fewer%20passes%20you'll%20need%20to%20finish%20the%20job.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThat%20being%20said%2C%20extra-wide%20mowers%20can%20sometimes%20struggle%20with%20hills%20and%20steep%20inclines%20and%20can%20have%20trouble%20maneuvering%20around%20landscaping%20features%2C%20ponds%2C%20and%20garden%20beds.%20A%20mower%20with%20a%20smaller%20deck%20might%20be%20a%20more%20practical%20choice%20in%20these%20cases%2C%20and%20even%20though%20they%20cut%20less%20grass%20on%20each%20pass%2C%20their%20superior%20mobility%20could%20get%20the%20job%20finished%20quicker%20in%20the%20end.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThis%20can%20be%20a%20lot%20to%20think%20about%2C%20which%20is%20why%20Blake%20mentioned%20the%20importance%20of%20consulting%20with%20an%20experienced%20outdoor%20power%20dealer%2C%20explaining%20that%20%26quot%3Bwhether%20you%20have%201%20acre%20or%2020%2C%20let%20your%20dealer%20help%20you%20with%20size%20so%20you%20don't%20buy%20too%20small%20or%20too%20big%2C%20since%20you%20want%20your%20choice%20to%20last%20you%20for%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Ch3%3EHow%20long%20is%20the%20average%20life%20of%20a%20riding%20mower%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EA%20riding%20mower%20can%20last%20up%20to%2010%20or%20even%2015%20years%20if%20it's%20taken%20care%20of%20properly%20and%20not%20regularly%20pushed%20past%20its%20limits.%20Just%20like%20a%20car%2C%20proper%20maintenance%20needs%20to%20be%20performed%20(oil%20changes%2C%20lubricating%20small%20components%2C%20replacing%20air%20filter%20and%20spark%20plugs%20annually)%20in%20order%20to%20ensure%20that%20your%20mower%20will%20last%20as%20long%20as%20possible.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EYou%20should%20also%20make%20sure%20to%20sharpen%20the%20blades%20at%20least%20once%20a%20season%20to%20ensure%20that%20you're%20not%20placing%20unnecessary%20strain%20on%20the%20engine.%20Make%20sure%20to%20thoroughly%20review%20your%20mower's%20use%20and%20care%20manual%20when%20you%20bring%20it%20home%20and%20consult%20with%20your%20retailer%20if%20you%20have%20any%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EWhat's%20the%20difference%20between%20a%20riding%20mower%20and%20lawn%20tractor%3F%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3ERiding%20mowers%20and%20lawn%20tractors%20can%20look%20the%20same%20%E2%80%94%20and%20they%20both%20cut%20grass%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20main%20difference%20is%20the%20jobs%20they're%20able%20to%20perform%20effectively.%20Riding%20mowers%20are%20designed%20primarily%20for%20cutting%20grass%2C%20and%20their%20front-mounted%20decks%20make%20them%20well-suited%20for%20it.%20This%20design%20allows%20you%20to%20easily%20maneuver%20around%20obstacles%20and%20makes%20it%20easier%20to%20see%20exactly%20what%20you're%20cutting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELawn%20tractors%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20have%20their%20deck%20mounted%20farther%20back%20in%20the%20center%20of%20the%20machine.%20This%20design%20results%20in%20a%20larger%20turning%20radius%20that%20can%20struggle%20with%20tight%20turns%20but%20also%20makes%20it%20easier%20for%20them%20to%20be%20used%20as%20a%20multifunctional%20machine.%20They%20can%20be%20customized%20with%20snowplows%20or%20blowers%20on%20the%20front%20and%20can%20easily%20pull%20spreaders%20or%20dump%20carts%20behind%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ECheck%20out%20our%20other%20lawn%20care%20guides%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22700%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22rake%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5e17725f24fe1251de6a4733%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22525%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EFiskars%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-rake%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20best%20rakes%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca